column2: FM: deleted space before SBATCH commands increased backup period for iae added run_state log to backup message

FM: ready to train predator and iae on leftraru ignored backups dir because apptainer works with a read-only filesystem, i.e. we need to mount it instead of copying it added separate scripts for training IAE and PREDATOR fixed typing errors
FM: fixed outdated numpy flags in the wrapper.cpp files, also added a pipefail to the cpp/compile step
FM: forgot to add some logs
FM: forgot to pass arguments in .sif file, added training mode to config
FM: now main expects a path to a config file, config file now controls the optimizer and which model gets trained
FM: added missing import dependencies to encoder
FM: fixed wrong version of torch scatter
FM: forgot to include IAE submodule in dockerfile
FM: added import_without_init function to basic.py, fixed small lsp errors
FM: working on adding more apptainer builds so we can run more jobs in parallel, also working on a script to manually test the feature extractors using the bunny model
FM: now base dockerfile is lighter and added apptainer configurations
FM: forgot to unpack sample in PREDATOR's validation step
now models can be saved and restored, also made prettier logs
FM: training now works with both PREDATOR and LIM, LIM can train with PREDATOR's encoder. Also changed windows compose file
FM: some code reorganization
FM: now PREDATOR is fully parametrized
FM: some code cleanup
FM: finally predator training is working on my  own implementation, I had made some mistakes implementing KPConv
FM: fixed cuda runtime error, BottleNeck class had a tensor with gradients added decorator to handle cuda out of memory error found new bug where around iteration 300 features tensor is full of nans
FM: refactored losses, now they log on aim on their own and MultiLoss is a generic class which can combine any number of losses
FM: now cuda OOM errors are handled by keeping track of a downsample factor for each pair
FM: Predator is now training correctly, we still need ot check the parameters and compare with the original training curve

FM: fixed dimensions issues with predator neighbors and pool calculations, I should refactor that layer class to make Cloud work like linked lists between the levels of superpoints, added a debugging decorator
FM: forgot to add these files in last commit
FM: wip, own predator implementation almost done
FM: wip overlappredator
FM: now we track both losses on train and val, added a docker compose file to train geotransformer
FM: some fixes, IAE training works again
FM: now tracking both losses on training and validation, added cosineannealingLR scheduler
FM: restored some accidentaly deleted imports, best validation model is now saved
FM: added yaml config file, now IAE receives an encoder as an argument, we backup the best validation model
FM: fixed IAE model, turns out defining the layers as plain lists is a bad idea, they don't train
FM: added network to host in docker so we can use aim
FM: added some submodules, added tensor shape annotations to DGCNNEncoder
FM: small fixes
FM: now it really works with the gpu
FM: added missing submodules
FM: submodules were being ignored
FM: almost done adding validation step
FM: more entrypoint shenanigans
FM: git typo on entrypoint.sh
FM: submodules aren't loading correctly
FM: docker compose windows entrypoint shenanigans
FM: testing on windows machine
FM: enabled support for cuda, now torch and open3d use tensors, also added docker compose file to run the project in a rocm container
FM: reworked Cloud class so now it can create objects from a path, a pcd or an array. Also, forgot to add src/ folder in previous commit
FM: IAE should be working now with individual samples
FM: finally figured out what does the IAE encoder receive as input, I wrote it in the scanNet class
FM: added scannet dataset
FM: a bit of refactoring, moved pcd visualization utility to Pairs class
FM: I made a mistake on the .gitignore and the dataset classes were being excluded
FM: predator and 3dlomatch now working as intended
FM: added script to download datasets, still needs some work but it's fine for now
Initial commit
